article.headline: North Texas 74, Arkansas St. 50
article.story: DENTON, Texas -- Alzee Williams scored 19 points on Thursday night and North Texas rolled to a 74-50 victory over Arkansas State. North Texas (12-19, 7-13 Sun Belt) also got 16 points and three steals from Jordan Williams, 12 points and three steals from Roger Franklin and 10 points, 13 rebounds and three blocked shots from Tony Mitchell. Arkansas State (18-10, 12-7) got 18 points from Marcus Hooten and 14 points from Ed Townsel. Trey Finn had nine rebounds for Arkansas State and Kendrick Washington had eight rebounds. Arkansas State made just 25 percent of its shots for the game and was only 1 of 23 from 3-point range.
